{
  "texts": [
    "Knowledge grounding refers to generating the necessary implicit knowledge that the model will use to understand the contradiction in the input statement.",
    "Unlike traditional approaches that rely on retrieving information from static commonsense knowledge bases, which often suffer from sparsity issues and may result in no-hit scenarios (where no relevant knowledge is found), our framework leverages LLMs to generate the implicit knowledge dynamically.",
    "This ensures that the model accesses a broader, more contextually appropriate set of information tailored to the specific concepts and context, thereby establishing a more robust foundation for explanation generation.",
    "Once the knowledge grounding is complete, the explanation generation phase uses the grounded implicit knowledge to construct a prompt that guides the LLM in producing an explanation.",
    "This knowledge-augmented prompt allows the model not only to be aware of the commonsense contradiction in the statement but also to provide a clear and logical explanation that explains why the nonsensical statement contradicts commonsense."
  ]
}